{
  "text": "Native cyanobacterial genetic parts were amplified from genomic DNA using NEB Q5 High-Fidelity DNA Polymerase (New England Biolabs) ( Fig. 1 ; Supp. Info. 1). Where necessary, native genetic parts were domesticated (i.e. BsaI and BpiI sites were removed) using specific primers. Alternatively, parts were synthesised as Gblocks \u00ae DNA fragments (Integrated DNA Technology) and cloned directly into an appropriate level 0 acceptor (see Supp. Info. 2 for vector maps) [CITATION_1] .",
